<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hook1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hook,</orth> subst. any thing bent into a curve: <cit><quote>a pair of anchoring --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a Welsh h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.373" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 373</bibl></cit> (a sort of bill curved at the end). Chiefly the curvated iron on which the bait is hung for fishes: <bibl n="shak. luc 103" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 137.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 137, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 171</bibl> (cf. <emph>Hold</emph>). <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 167</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>